abstract: >-
  This paper explores the relationship between ethnic diversity and conflict in Sub-Saharan Africa. Based on a novel measure exploring similarity in oral traditions, I explore a wide range of mediators, such as intergroup contact, the relationship to ethnic identity, and content.
